        viewModelScope.launch {
            repository.login(email, password)
                .collect { apiState ->
                    when (apiState) {
                        is ApiState.Success -> {
                            _loginState.value = apiState
                            Timber.d("Login successful: ${apiState.data}")
                        }
                        is ApiState.Failure -> {
                            _loginState.value = apiState
                            Timber.e("Login failed: ${apiState.errorMessage}")
                        }
                        else -> {
                            // Handle other cases if needed
                        }
                    }
                }
        }
    }
}
```

In the updated code, when the `apiState` is an instance of `ApiState.Success`, we log the success message using `Timber.d("Login successful: ${apiState.data}")`. The `apiState.data` property contains the `LoginResponse` object.

Additionally, we also log the error message when the `apiState` is an instance of `ApiState.Failure` using `Timber.e("Login failed: ${apiState.errorMessage}")`.

Make sure you have the `Timber` logging library set up correctly in your project. If you're using Timber, you should initialize it in your application class or a custom application class. For example:

